<% 
  provide(:full_title, "Badge List - Mapping human knowledge.")
%>

<div class="row-fluid banner-row">
  <div class="span8 offset2">
    <h1>
      <%= image_tag 'badge-list-icon-orange.png' %>
      Badge List
    </h1>
    <span class="tag-line">Helping organizations turn achievements into social currency.</span>
    <div class="vertical-line">&nbsp;</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row-fluid sub-banner-row">
  <div class="span8 offset2">
    <div class="vertical-line top">&nbsp;</div>
    <ul class="details">
      <li>
        <i class="fa fa-trophy"></i>
        Badges represent <strong>skills and achievements</strong>
      </li>
      <li class="separator"><span>&nbsp;</span></li>
      <li>
        <i class="fa fa-list-alt"></i>
        Awarded badges contain <strong>evidence</strong> and expert <strong>validation</strong>
      </li>
      <li class="separator"><span>&nbsp;</span></li>
      <li>
        <i class="fa fa-share-alt"></i>
        Badges are <strong>easy to share</strong> on social networks and blogs
      </li>
      <li class="separator"><span>&nbsp;</span></li>
      <li>
        <i class="fa fa-group"></i>
        Badges are building blocks for <strong>vibrant online communities</strong>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div class="vertical-line bottom">&nbsp;</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row-fluid header-row">
  <div class="span8 offset2">
    <h2>How does it work?</h2>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row-fluid number-row">
  <div class="span8 offset2 row-inner">
    <span class="number">1</span>
    <h3>Build your badges</h3>
    
    <span class="details">
      Each badge belongs to a specific learning group which represents your organization or 
      community. Group admins collaborate to create a collection of badges representing important
      achievements. Use Badge List's built-in badge designer or upload your own design.
    </span>

    <span class="list-header">
      Badge Examples
    </span>

    <ul class="examples">
      <li>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" title="">
          <%= image_tag 'badge-list-icon-50.png', title: 'Alt Text', alt: 'Alt Text' %>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" title="">
          <%= image_tag 'badge-list-icon-50.png', title: 'Alt Text', alt: 'Alt Text' %>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" title="">
          <%= image_tag 'badge-list-icon-50.png', title: 'Alt Text', alt: 'Alt Text' %>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row-fluid number-row dark">
  <div class="span8 offset2 row-inner">
    <span class="number">2</span>
    <h3>Define required evidence</h3>
    
    <span class="details">
      Build out each badge by defining a list of evidence which must be submitted in order to 
      receive the badge. Badge List supports many evidence formats including uploaded images,
      linked tweets and snippets of computer code. Everything is mobile-friendly.
    </span>

    <span class="list-header">
      Evidence Formats
    </span>

    <ul class="examples">
      <li>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" title="">
          <%= image_tag 'badge-list-icon-50.png', title: 'Alt Text', alt: 'Alt Text' %>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" title="">
          <%= image_tag 'badge-list-icon-50.png', title: 'Alt Text', alt: 'Alt Text' %>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" title="">
          <%= image_tag 'badge-list-icon-50.png', title: 'Alt Text', alt: 'Alt Text' %>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row-fluid number-row">
  <div class="span8 offset2 row-inner">
    <span class="number">3</span>
    <h3>Award badges</h3>
    
    <span class="details">
      After a badge seeker submits all of the evidence their achievement is validated by an
      approved badge awarder. The badge is then awarded and added to their Badge List profile. 
      The new badge holder can then share their achievement to social networks.
    </span>

    <span class="list-header">
      Actual User Profiles
    </span>

    <ul class="examples">
      <li>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" title="">
          <%= image_tag 'badge-list-icon-50.png', title: 'Alt Text', alt: 'Alt Text' %>
